verbose_text: In spite of the very low levels of recombinant APOPT1 in transduced individual S2 immortalized fibroblasts, we found a small but consistent increase in the amounts of cIV and supercomplex cIII+ cIV in these cells compared to naive individual S2 cells (XREF_FIG B and 5C), suggesting a role for APOPT1 in cIV assembly and/or stability.
